com.isotrol.impe3.nr.api
Class NodeFilter

java.lang.Object
  com.isotrol.impe3.nr.api.NodeFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
IsEmptyFlag, IsNullFlag, Serializable
public abstract class NodeFilter
extends Object
implements Serializable, IsEmptyFlag, IsNullFlag

Node filter. A null filter performs no filtering. An empty filter always returns an empty result. Filters are "joined" in the the sense that operations are applied in order with the following criteria:

  • A null filter performs no filtering.
  • For an empty filter every operation returns the empty filter.
  • Once due nodes are requested, undue nodes will never be returned.
  • For filter maps, OPTIONAL elements are OR'd together. The resulting filter is NOT'd with the FORBIDDEN and the resulting is AND'd with the REQUIRED.
  • For the categories map, the uncategorized property is treated as another entry.

Author:
Emilio Escobar Reyero, Andres Rodriguez
